!begin_node Load file
!index Load
!html_name load_hv

!stg_limage [off]
!image (!IMAGES)stg_load
!stg_limage [on]
!begin_xlist [~~~~~~]
!item [~~~~~~] With this function one can load a hypertext or an ASCII file,
with the type being recognised automatically. A file selector
will appear in which the desired file may be selected, after
which this will be loaded, provided there is sufficient memory
available. The key combination for this function is incidentally
(!key [Control + O]).

The preselected path in the file selector will be chosen in the
following manner:
!begin_enumerate !compressed
!item Variable HYPFOLD (in the file ST-GUIDE.INF), if this
exists,
!item Path of the file last loaded, if HYPFOLD does not exist,
or
!item Current path, if no file has yet been loaded and HYPFOLD
does not exist.
!end_enumerate

The file extension mask will normally be preset to 'HYP'.

If the file to be selected is not a hypertext, then holding down
Shift when clicking on the icon or using the (!link [keyboard] [Keyboard functions]) shortcut
will bring up the file selector with '*.*' preselected. After a
file is selected, ST-Guide proceeds as follows:

!begin_enumerate !compressed
!item The extension of the selected file will be searched for as
a variable in the INF file (i.e. 'IMG=' for a file named
PICTURE.IMG)
!item If 1. is unsuccessful, the variable EXTVIEW will be
searched for in the INF file
!item If 1 and 2. were unsuccessful, ST-Guide will itself
display the file in ASCII format, otherwise the assigned
program will be searched for first under already running
applications, and if not found there ST-Guide will cause
the desktop to start the corresponding program. The last
will however only work if the desktop used has the
appropriate functions available, i.e. if it has
implemented the AV protocol.
!end_enumerate

If an AV-capable desktop is in use then the file to be displayed
can also be dragged directly to the ST-Guide window.
!end_xlist

