!begin_node* Pattern not found
!html_name err1
!ifdest [stg]
!label- %e1
!endif

The requested pattern could not be found.

Possible causes:

!begin_itemize
!item You have searched for a particular idea in a page, but no page exists
in the current hypertext.

Remedy: Try modifying your idea and looking again, or look in the
index.

!item You have found the idea in the current page and come to a stop.

Remedy: Try modifying your idea and looking again, or find it in an
earlier page that is thematically the same idea.

!item The REF-file of the hypertext that recognises the idea your looking
for, could not be searched.

Remedy: Use RefLink or RefCheck, to add in the relevant REF file.

!item You don't have any hypertexts on your disk that recognise the idea
your looking for.

Remedy: Perhaps you introduce a suitable hypertext for it?

!end_itemize

!end_node


!begin_node* File not found
!html_name err3
!ifdest [stg]
!label- %e3
!endif

The hypertext that the recognised idea your looking for, is in can not
be found, although its REF-file still exists.

Possible causes:

!begin_itemize
!item You have erased the hypertext and not erased the REF-file.

Remedy: Use it RefLink or RefCheck to remove the "REF-body".

!item You still possess the hypertext, but ST-Guide can't find it because
it's located in a directory that can't be found.

Remedy: (!link [Copy] [Extra -> Copy]) the hypertext to the Guides directory i.e.. the one
that is defined in the ST-Guide.Inf file under "PATHS=", or extend
this line to include the directory where the hypertext is located.

!end_itemize

!end_node


!begin_node* REF-file not found
!html_name err4
!ifdest [stg]
!label- %e4
!endif

The REF-file could not be found.

Possible causes:

!begin_itemize
!item you have not created a REF-file.

Remedy: Use RefLink or RefCheck to create it.

!item You actually have a REF-file, however it is not defined correctly in
the ST-Guide.Inf file.

Remedy: Put it in your ST-Guide.Inf file in the "REF=" line, giving
the right path and names of the file, or copy its location of the
REF-file to the "REF=" line.
!end_itemize

!end_node


!begin_node* Program not found
!html_name err5
!ifdest [stg]
!label- %e5
!endif

A program should have been started from within the hypertext, but
didn't, even though its path is given in the ST-Guide.Inf.

Possible causes:

!begin_itemize
!item The author of the hypertext has forgotten to inform you how you need
to install it in your ST-Guide.Inf file.

Remedy: Ask the author of the relevant hypertext what you have to
do here.

!item You have forgotten to identify the necessary extensions in the
ST-Guide.Inf file.

Remedy: Put the missing ones in immediately.
!end_itemize

!end_node


!begin_node* File not generated
!html_name err6
!ifdest [stg]
!label- %e6
!endif

A file could not be created.

Possible causes:

!begin_itemize
!item Your data storage device (floppy/hard disk) is full to the limit.

Remedy: Delete some files or get a bigger data storage device.

!item There is a write protected file with the same name in the directory
you are trying to create your file.

Remedy: Delete it after removing the 'Read Only' attribute. This
can be done by selecting the 'Show (!link [Info] [Info Dialogue])' menu option' in the
Desktop.
!end_itemize

!end_node


!begin_node* HYP-File not found
!html_name err7
!ifdest [stg]
!label- %e7
!endif

The requested file was not found, therefore can't be displayed.

Possible causes:

!begin_itemize
!item You don't possess the file.

Remedy: Ask the author of the hypertext, i.e. the author of the
program,that ST-Guide has instructed you to find where to get the
file.

!item You actually possess the file, but it is in the archives or a folder
that is hidden from ST-Guide.

Remedy: Copy the file into the GUIDES directory i.e. in one of the
directories that is listed in the ST-GUIDE.INF file in the
'PATHS=' line, or include the directory where the file is located.

!item You have renamed the file.

Remedy: Give the file it's original name.
!end_itemize

!end_node

!end_document
